what_worked: Applied decorrelate, date_cte_isolate: Created a shared `week_dates` CTE to compute the target week dates once instead of three separate correlated subqueries, and introduced a `filtered_items` CTE to separate join/filter logic from final calculation. Also converted implicit joins to explicit JOIN syntax for better optimizer control.
why_it_worked: Correlated subqueries re-execute per outer row; converting to JOIN eliminates per-row overhead; Pre-filtering date dimension into CTE reduces hash join probe table from 73K to ~365 rows
